Constructor for polynomial with normal parametrization.

The polynomial is defined over the two variables x = m12, y = m13 as:

p(x,y) = c0 + c1*x + c2*y + c3*x^2 + c4*y^2 + c5*x*y + c6*x^3 + c7*y^3 + c8*x^2*y + c9*x*y^2

Constructor for polynomial with a symmetric/asymmetric parametrization.

The polynomial is defined over the two variables x = m12, y = m13 as:

p(x,y) = c0 + s1(x+y) + s2(x^2+y^2) + s3(x^3+y^3) + s4(yx^2+xy^2) + s5(xy) a1(x-y) + a2(x^2-y^2) + a3(x^3-y^3) + a4(yx^2-xy^2)

Must be called with any value for saParams to distinguish it from the default constructor.
